at runtime.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.SS check
.PP
.I Guided boot health check + repair (default action)
.PP
.B Category:
Diagnostics
.br
.B Maturity:
beta
.PP
.B SYNTAX
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
lamboot\-doctor [\-\-auto] [\-\-risk\-limit LEVEL] [\-\-no\-repair] [\-\-no\-clean] [\-\-offline DISK] [\-\-json]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B ARGUMENTS
.PP
.RS 4
.TP
.B \-\-auto
Non\-interactive; still confirms typed\-yes for critical findings
.TP
.B \-\-risk\-limit LEVEL
safe
.TP
.B moderate
moderate
.TP
.B destructive (default
 moderate)
.TP
.B \-\-no\-repair
Diagnose + show plan; don\'t invoke repair
.TP
.B \-\-no\-clean
Skip ESP clean actions even if they would apply
.TP
.B \-\-offline DISK
Operate against a disk image; propagates to diagnose/repair/esp/backup
.RE
.PP
.B EXAMPLES
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
sudo lamboot\-doctor
lamboot\-doctor \-\-no\-repair
sudo lamboot\-doctor \-\-auto
lamboot\-doctor \-\-offline /dev/pve/vm\-201\-disk\-1 \-\-no\-repair
lamboot\-doctor \-\-json 
 jq .context.plan
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B NOTES
.PP
.RS 4
Chains lamboot\-diagnose → policy matrix → lamboot\-repair / lamboot\-esp clean. Never invokes lamboot\-migrate automatically (always user\-initiated). Sudo escalation happens at most once per run. Offline mode propagates the \-\-offline DISK flag to every sub\-tool invocation; the disk is attached once by diagnose, findings guide offline\-safe repairs, and teardown happens automatically at exit.
.RE
.PP
.B OFFLINE:
Yes \- supports \fB\-\-offline\fR \fIDISK\fR
